FBIS4-19738 "drweu078_j_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-078 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY ANSA Journalists Strike To Protest Job Cuts ANSA Journalists Strike To Protest Job Cuts LD2104153594 Rome RAI Uno Television Network in Italian 1130 GMT 21 Apr 94 LD2104153594 Rome RAI Uno Television Network Italian BFN [Text] Journalists from ANSA, Italy's largest press agency, began a three-day strike yesterday afternoon to protest against the company's reorganization plan, which envisages a drastic cut in the number of journalists. According to a document released by the strike committee, the plan, apart from not providing adequately for the company's reorganization and relaunch, also carries serious repercussions for the quality of news items produced.
